[TextBlock(citations=None, text='Here is a Python script to list unread emails:\n\n```python\nimport imaplib\nimport email\nfrom email.header import decode_header\nimport webbrowser\nimport os\n\n# account credentials\nusername = "your_email@example.com"  \npassword = "your_email_password"\n\n# create an IMAP4 class with SSL \nimap = imaplib.IMAP4_SSL("imap.gmail.com")\n# authenticate\nimap.login(username, password)\n\nstatus, messages = imap.select("INBOX")\n# number of unread messages\nN = int(messages[0]) \n\nfor i in range(N, 0, -1):\n    # fetch email message by ID\n    res, msg = imap.fetch(str(i), "(RFC822)")\n    for response in msg:\n        if isinstance(response, tuple):\n            # parse email into an email object\n            msg = email.message_from_bytes(response[1])\n            # decode email subject\n            subject = decode_header(msg["Subject"])[0][0]\n            if isinstance(subject, bytes):\n                subject = subject.decode()\n            print(f"Unread email: {subject}")\n\nimap.close()\nimap.logout()\n```\n\nThis script imports the IMAP library to connect to the inbox, iterates through unread emails, and prints out the unread email subjects. The credentials will need to be configured. Let me know if you have any other questions!', type='text')]